            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-24 11:34:38" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to be in a state of hunger, without any implications of particular contributing circumstances</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be hungry</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to have hunger</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Hunger is often spoken of in an idiomatic manner, for example, ‘my stomach is crying,’ ‘my throat has been cut’ (implying that one has not been able to swallow food for a long time), or ‘my stomach is a deep hole.’</Comments>
